{"ID":270368, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"368\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs367.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs369.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 368<\/div>\n  <p class=\"cont\">born to die, and all men must rise;<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span> all must enter eternity.<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">In order for you to receive your children to yourselves you must have a promise&mdash;some\n  ordinance; some blessing,<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span> in order to ascend above principalities,<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span> or else it may be an angel.<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> They\n  must rise just as they died;<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span> we can there hail our lovely infants with the same glory&mdash;the same\n  loveliness in the celestial glory,<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span> where they all enjoy alike.<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span> They differ in stature, in size, the same\n  glorious spirit gives them the likeness of glory and bloom; the old man with his silvery hairs will\n  glory in bloom and beauty. No man can describe it to you&mdash;no man can write it.<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">When did I ever teach anything wrong from this stand? When was I ever confounded? I want\n  to triumph in Israel<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span> before I depart hence and am no more seen.<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span> I never told you I was perfect;\n  but there is no error in the revelations which I have taught. Must I, then, be thrown away as a thing\n  of naught?<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">I enjoin for your consideration&mdash;add to your faith, virtue, love, &amp;c. I say, in the name of the\n  Lord, if these things are in you, you shall be fruitful.<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span> I testify that no man has power to reveal it\n  but myself<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span>&mdash;things in heaven, in earth,<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span> and hell; and all shut your mouths for the future. I\n  commend you all to God,<span class=\"footRef\">16<\/span> that you may inherit all things;<span class=\"footRef\">17<\/span> and may God add His blessing. Amen.\n  (May 12, 1844.) DHC 6:363-367.<\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">The Prophet&rsquo;s Dreams on Conditions of Apostates at Nauvoo<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">In the evening I attended meeting in the Seventies&rsquo; Hall. George J. Adams preached and I made\n  some observations afterwards, and related a dream which I had a short time since. I thought I was\n  riding out in my carriage, and my guardian angel was along with me. We went past the Temple and\n  had not gone much further before we espied two large snakes so fast locked together that neither of\n  them had any power. I inquired<span class=\"footRef\">18<\/span> of my guide what I was to understand by that. He answered,\n  &ldquo;Those snakes represent Dr. Foster and Chauncey L. Higbee. They are your enemies and desire to\n  destroy you;<span class=\"footRef\">19<\/span> but you see they are so fast locked together that they have no power of themselves\n  to hurt you.&rdquo;  I then thought I was riding up Mulholland street, but my guardian angel was not along\n  with me. On arriving at the prairie, I was overtaken<\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109584\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109584)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109584)\">1 Cor. 15:21-22<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111890\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111890)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111890)\">Alma 11:41<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">3. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116332\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclic